            "name": "Eliran Sobel",
            "bio": "Eliran Sobel is a rabbinical student at Yeshivat Chovevei Torah. He is a graduate of Rutgers University, majoring in Linguistics with a minor in Jewish Studies, and has spent time learning at the Hadar Institute and the Pardes Institute of Jewish Studies. He has had internships with institutions such as the Jewish English Lexicon, SAR Academy, and Shamayim: Jewish Animal Advocacy. He is passionate about veganism, Yiddish, and  is particularly interested in the variety of nusḥa'ot and studying Tana'kh and liturgy.",
            "website": "",
